# Experiment No.2:  

The aim of this experiment is to implement the concept of If-else and Nested if else. 

#A. Write a Java program to accept two numbers from the user and display the greater number using an 
if-else statement. 
B. Write a Java program to accept three numbers from the user and display the greatest number using 
if-else statements. 
C. Write a Java program to check whether a given number is odd or even using an if-else statement. 
D. Write a Java program to check whether a student has passed or failed based on marks.

import java.util.Scanner;

class GreaterOfTwo {
  public static void main(String[] args) {
    Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
    System.out.print("Enter two number: ");
    int a = sc.nextInt(), b = sc.nextInt();
    if (a > b) 
      System.out.println("Greater: " + a);
      else 
      System.out.println("Greater: " + b);
    }
  }
